om their admin no other categories.&nbsp;&nbsp;So the owner would be super admin.&nbsp;&nbsp;They would appoint 4 admins for each of 4 categories.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each admin could only see their own category unless authorized by super admin.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nAdmins and users need name, username and password only.&nbsp;&nbsp;Only admins and users can see the database otherwise it is not viewable to anyone.<br />\n<br />\nWhen a new entry is added to the database and email should be sent to their admin and all the users under that admin.&nbsp;&nbsp;This email should show who got added and&nbsp;&nbsp;the ability to rate the freelancer.&nbsp;&nbsp;They should be able to rate from insides the email without clicking on a link.&nbsp;&nbsp;One rating per user on the initial rating email.&nbsp;&nbsp;Admin has the ability to change the rating overriding all votes in the system.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When a tour is over the admin and users should receive an email that says The tour is over, please rate your crew from this tour.&nbsp;&nbsp;Display the name and picture of each crew member along with the ability to rate the crew member again.&nbsp;&nbsp;This rating should be shown next to the tour in their experience.&nbsp;&nbsp;Ratings should be NEW 1-10 and a 0 which says never hire.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;New 	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2 &hellip;.<br />\n<br />\n0&rsquo;s should not show up in search results.&nbsp;&nbsp;At the end of the search results there should be a link that says &ldquo;show crew with 0 rating&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nAdd freelancer and user to database should be buttons from the home screen.&nbsp;&nbsp;When add freelancer is clicked an email address is entered.&nbsp;&nbsp;Form that is emailed is similar to the directory search with either blank boxes or a list the ability to check off your skills.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\n<br />\nDatabase needs to be